The need for speed The Run is being fought across America.
Revision
Originally a run without problems is transformed because of a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do in a routine morning commute to work.
It fulfills to some extent the ambition of everyone but it is useless if no one wants to do something more.
The new subtitled part The Run produced high expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already old Need for Speed racing series and release a kind of game from the playable games that would not count only with points.
So we were curious how the added passages will be when the main hero gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole thing pulls down because of a few unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes but rather the expression of incomprehensible laziness on the part of the developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are caught up in the adventure whose main hero Jack has character problems and to solve them starts to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has some interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then over 50 races.
As a result, each race takes place on a different route and the planned stages in different environments that stand out quite well from each other and are interesting.
The player does not feel for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are also pretty even if the graphical technical level is the same as the previous series.
Well, it's not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very pleasant visually.
The tests are in addition from time to time embellished with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly decreases your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Alongside this, the different races are well arranged one after the other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
There are moments you strive to surpass the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you race against the clock (classic duel with the stopwatch) and then again you await another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police coming into the game and trying to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty is the out-of-vehicle passages.
Rather, it’s an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help them by tapping the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is well like this because this element does not risk to hinder and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that embellish the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that at present there is nothing extraordinary but it cannot be said that it is negative.
For realistic simulation you will have to go elsewhere.
But although we can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything is ok.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not yet at the point.
We don't expect this game to be complicated deformation and collisions, but when you don't have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, it's not completely good.
During tight overtakings you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car goes into crazy flights.
Or it ends up in crumbs.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done in such a way that when you have broken your figure or you have gone out into the scenery the game brings you back to the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used all 5 restarts you have to start the game again from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go right, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes the restarts do not help and the solution must be found by remembering the piece of route in question.
The big draw of this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are certain turns that must be passed in a certain way otherwise it does not pass.
Otherwise you meet on a given place "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or one minute late.
What makes you angry is the situations when you see the opponent easily pass between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either stand aside and bypass them or brake.
It does not matter if you go ahead of him because it is "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation it always happens very close to your nose.
Adversaries have other advantages.
During all the time of the game, you, you arrive in certain places, again without worrying about the weather, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This annoys the most at the end of the game when you ride on a long deck in the opposite direction.
The opponent must pass in front of you at all costs.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collide a good number of times.
It can be understood that the purpose of this game is to do something captivating and full of adredalin,but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it's a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that happens.
And it doesn't matter if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, the order of the races is such that there's no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is to change the car during the races.
You need to be careful about gasoline pumps on the routes because you can change cars there however most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American engines for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic features on highly technical roads, for example on laced roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places that you know of adventure, goes very well with the main regime of the story.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock themselves:
This one connects online with the Autolog function which among other things compares your results with those of other players and gives you other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult strokes to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks like).
Your speed indicator tells you between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you comes a subway train that sends the car directly to the scrap.
At the editorial board we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought about creating this game or whether the authors really think we are idiots.
The technical part of the game is not extra,but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What is bothering is that in more extreme situations, imaging does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This applies especially to accidents with a large number of participants when fluid imaging is no longer useful.
The sound part is good and the track is to choose from.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the most young audience a new soundtrack has been created in the style "I mix everything", but we can expect that no one will buy the game for the music.
Overall impression of Need for Speed: The Run is really confusing.
If the game didn’t have those stupid mistakes we could say without fear that it is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game gives the impression of not being finished.
The fun is really good but be prepared for faults to hit you in the eye with the force of an aerodrome reflector.
The Velvet Students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival perform 20 choirs of high schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival consists of two concerts organized on November 17.
“Charles University plays an important part in this festival.”
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the festival committee sits the rector Vaclav Hampl," says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir of High Schools and Secondary Classes which takes place with free entry on November 17 from 2 p.m. on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening takes place the concert "Students of velvet"in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of the Charles University.
The objective of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate with dignity the International Student Day and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public choir music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organiser is the Union of Czech Scholars in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program offers in addition to high-level concerts, mic meetings, student happening and other activities.
Interested parties will find all the information on the festival's website www.festaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
Czechs Behaving Like Negativists and Eurosceptics
"The Lisbon Treaty has radically removed the balance between the institutions"
“I didn’t expect such a tough war.”
"It will take 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all players get used to their new role," Miléna Vicenova began her presentation at the Faculty of Law the Czech ambassador to the European Union.
When she managed to describe the various EU bodies and their relations in such an understandable and visible way, to the point that a large number of lecturers at the Charles University Law School might envy her, she showed how much she takes her motto "understandably and openly about Europe" very seriously.
Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new Permanent President of the European Council.
“From the beginning, there was criticism that he’s faded, that he’s a leatherback, that he can’t fulfill any mission, and I have to say that he took everyone’s breath away because he holds his role to perfection.”
“He is a man who knows how to listen to 27 member states, communicate well with them and has a clear vision of the direction to take from Europe.”
She explained the new post of the High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy as part of an answer to the question: "Who is who in the European Union?" "To what phone number should I call?", thus as an important step towards the uniqueness and greater legibility of the Union's policy vis-à-vis states, such as China or India.
Nobody wants to forbid us our syrecky (cooked cheese that smells very strong)
Mrs Vicenova also referred to the agenda that the European Council has lived, lives and will live in the near future.
She described the Czech Presidency as successful two years ago.
The Czechs either resolved the rising financial crisis, the gas crisis or organized an Eastern Partnership Summit.
It called the fall of the government very negative and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
The Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
In the words of the Ambassador, "the activity has reached its peak" not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis that continues to be resolved now.
In addition, we must approve the new seventh budget of the Union, which is becoming very complicated due to the current economic situation.
Since it would seem that the budget will be thin and for savings, which branch will have priority, which countries will be helped the most, the least, everything is to be resolved in the framework of future negotiations.
The Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For a comprehensible Europe".
“I really don’t like abbreviations, foreign words, jargon that nobody understands.
As the citizen must understand that it is true that in Brussels no one makes round or twisted pickles, bananas differently large or that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky.
It wants to make better use of the EU environment and see more Czechs in the European institutions.
A multi-speed Europe awaits us
According to the Ambassador the Czechs have a reputation for being Eurosceptics and people who see things only in their negative aspect more than positively.
Moreover, she is sorry to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
The fault, she said, stemmed from a number of factors, such as the shyness of our candidates, their inability to write a cover letter and weak support from the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech Presidency, she then underlined the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
"Believe me, when the Pole, the Magyar, the Slovak come to me, that Frenchman says to me, 'Hey, what are you doing there, what is this group from Visegrad still doing?' and he's not happy at all."
According to Mrs Vicenova, in the near future, tough new rules on fiscal policy await the Member States.
This is the concept of a Europe with two speeds, if not several speeds, which prevails rather than a "new European Federation".
“We have countries in the eurozone and others outside the eurozone.”
"We have the Schengen area, we also have the Institute for Enhanced Cooperation."
In the first place it was said that the countries that want to cooperate with each other and those that do not want to stay in their corner.
"There will be a lot of institutes of this type and there will be a really two-speed Europe," Vicenova expects.
From this point of view, she also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to establish the basis on which all issues having an impact on the EU should be debated between all EU members and not only eurozone members.
History of a brand:
IBM Innovator Begins the Second Century of Its Existence
If someone were to look for the word that most closely expresses the IBM strategy, the closest would be "the long term".
For a wide audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a firm felt as very current and yet since its creation it has been a hundred years.
The foundation for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm’s first head, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left this slogan that a lot of global problems can be solved as long as people are willing to think.
His slogan "THINK!" became the imprint around which the life of a future giant would develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
This was the basis of Watson's carefully crafted company culture.
For us IBM means a long-term thinking of continuous movements directed towards the future.
IBM has survived a hundred years thanks to the fact that it has always remained true to its core values and yet has not been afraid to change all the others around it.
This has enabled us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will achieve even more"said for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the thirties, began to take care of his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - the IBM people were the only ones among the first American employees to have paid vacations, employer-paid insurance plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-developed system of rewards for inventors and traders.
In the same way, IBM has a well-developed system of customer relations.
At first, the company was great at discovering talent – as one of the first firms to abolish all forms of discrimination and thus had a choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman – Virginia Rometty – who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has worked at IBM for 30 years and is currently Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
In recent years, IBM has been doing what is called jamy, online brainstorming, from which many future strategies and innovations have emerged.
