Pierre Deschamps, a specialist in health law, called the position of the experts signing the report "extreme", among other things because it does not limit the practice of euthanasia to terminally ill patients.
"This opens the door to a situation where anyone who is tired of life and is over 18 years old could ask for help to commit suicide," said Deschamps, who consulted a summary of the report yesterday.
Deschamps also points out that the authors of the report seem to place the autonomy of the person above all other values that participate in the social fabric of society.
"In society," he says, "there are beacons and constraints."
Health law expert Margaret Somerville also expressed “strong opposition” to the report’s findings, which she called a “pro-euthanasia manifesto.”
