Austria responds to a request from the eurozone summit in Brussels on 26 October: the heads of state and government had then called for the inclusion by the end of 2012 of the reduction of public deficits and a return to the balance of public accounts in the constitution or in a law of the same value.
The arrangement adopted by the Austrian government is close to the "German model", with Germany being the first European country to adopt such a "rule".
By 2017, the structural government deficit will have to decrease each year by 0.75% of the Gross Domestic Product (GDP) and, from 2017, the structural government deficit of the federal state will not have to exceed 0.35% of GDP each year, while the regional states and municipalities will have to present balanced budgets.
The objective is to bring public debt under the 60% criterion set by the Maastricht Treaty by 2020/21.
